{"task_id": "sliding-window-maximum", "question_id": 239, "difficulty": "Hard", "tags": ["Queue", "Array", "Sliding Window", "Monotonic Queue", "Heap (Priority Queue)"], "problem_description": "You are given an array of integers nums, there is a sliding window of size k which is moving from the very left of the array to the very right. You can only see the k numbers in the window. Each time the sliding window moves right by one position.\nReturn the max sliding window.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [1,3,-1,-3,5,3,6,7], k = 3\nOutput: [3,3,5,5,6,7]\nExplanation: \nWindow position                Max\n---------------               -----\n[1  3  -1] -3  5  3  6  7       3\n 1 [3  -1  -3] 5  3  6  7       3\n 1  3 [-1  -3  5] 3  6  7       5\n 1  3  -1 [-3  5  3] 6  7       5\n 1  3  -1  -3 [5  3  6] 7       6\n 1  3  -1  -3  5 [3  6  7]      7\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [1], k = 1\nOutput: [1]\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 105\n-104 <= nums[i] <= 104\n1 <= k <= nums.length\n\n", "starter_code": "class Solution:\n    def maxSlidingWindow(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> List[int]:\n        ", "completion": "class Solution:\n    def maxSlidingWindow(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> List[int]:\n        q = [(-v, i) for i, v in enumerate(nums[: k - 1])]\n        heapify(q)\n        ans = []\n        for i in range(k - 1, len(nums)):\n            heappush(q, (-nums[i], i))\n            while q[0][1] <= i - k:\n                heappop(q)\n            ans.append(-q[0][0])\n        return ans\n", "entry_point": "Solution().maxSlidingWindow", "test": "def check(candidate):\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, 3, -1, -3, 5, 3, 6, 7],k = 3) == [3, 3, 5, 5, 6, 7]\n    assert candidate(nums = [5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5],k = 5) == [5, 5, 5, 5, 5]\n    assert candidate(nums = [4, -2],k = 2) == [4]\n    assert candidate(nums = [9, 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1],k = 4) == [9, 8, 7, 6, 5, 4]\n    assert candidate(nums = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9],k = 2) == [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8,